HEADWORD: Translocation
<hw>Trans`lo*ca"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>trans-</ets> + <ets>location</ets>.]</ety> <def>removal of things
from one place to another; substitution of one thing for
another.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>There happened certain <qex>translocations</qex> at the
deluge.</q> <rj><qau>Woodward.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

